 Press release 

 
 





  November 16,  2015</strong>  36-Hour Hackathon takes over eSports Arena Nov. 20-22</strong>  


    EVENT:  
       Over 400 student hackers from around Southern California will battle it out for 36 hours in Santa Ana’s eSports Arena for HackUCI. 
      WHEN/WHERE: 
       Friday, Nov. 20 at 7 p.m. – Sunday, Nov. 22 at 4 p.m.  
          (Official contest runs from Nov. 20 at 11 p.m. to Nov. 22 at 11 a.m.)
           
          eSports Arena is located at 120 W. 5th St, Santa Ana, CA 92701 
          ( Google Map ).  

            
          Parking options:
             Parking lot opposite eSports Arena
               Parking meters on the street
               Intersection of East 5th/Main or Intersection of West 3rd/Broadway
             
      INFORMATION: 
       Media planning to attend can contact Matt Miller at 949-824-1562 or  matt.miller@uci.edu . We will have a photographer attending the event, and we will be able to share photos and video following the event.
       
      HIGHLIGHTS: 
       Doors Open to Students – Nov. 20 at 7 p.m. 

Event Kickoff – Nov. 20 at 9 p.m. 

Closing Ceremony – Nov. 22 at 3 p.m.
       
      BACKGROUND: 
       A hackathon is a place where people come together and build whatever technological project they can come up with. Professional mentors may be present, but attendees may find that their best source of help is from other hackers. HackUCI sponsors include Cylance, Microsoft, IBM, Facebook and many others. For more information on the event, visit  http://hackuci.com 
       
       
 
 
  
